David Cameron said he was an Aston Villa fan 'all his life' He was giving a speech in south London on Saturday when he said he supported West Ham United . 
  Prime Minister flew over Upton Park ground on way back from Clacton in Essex on Friday . 
  He said he had been past the ground the day before but could not remember which club he supported . 
  Mr Cameron insisted he was a Villa fan because his uncle was 'involved in the club' But he was ridiculed by Labour for naming another club instead of his own . 
  He insisted he has been an Villa fan since watching the 1982 European Cup final . 
 